    @Deprecated
public abstract class PipeInputIterator
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.util.Iterator<Instance>
    Interface for classes that generate instances. Typically, these instances will be unprocessed (e.g., they may come from a corpusimport data file), and are passed through a pipe as they are added to an InstanceList.
    See Also:
    Pipe, InstanceList
